5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to criminal law; to amend Section 13A-3-23,
10 Code of Alabama 1975, to further provide for the justification
11 of using physical force in defense of self or an individual;
12 to establish a presumption that the use of force in defense of
13 self or another is not justified when a defendant engages in
14 certain conduct.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Section 13A-3-23, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§13A-3-23
19 (a) A person is justified in using physical force upon
20 another person in order to when both of the following are
21 satisfied:
22 (1) The person's use of force is to defend himself or
23 herself or a third person from what he or she reasonably
24 believes to be the use or imminent use of unlawful physical
25 force by anotherthat other person, and he or she may use.
26 (2) The person uses a degree of force which he or she
27 reasonably believes to be necessary for the purpose.
28 (b)(1) A person may use deadly physical force, and is
Page 1

(b)(1) A person may use deadly physical force, and is
