85 his or her ground.
86 (c)(d) Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (a)
87 or (b), a person is not justified in using physical force if
88 any of the following apply:
89 (1) With intent to cause physical injury or death to
90 another person, he or she provoked the use of unlawful
91 physical force by such the other person.
92 (2) He or she was the initial aggressor, except that
93 his or her use of physical force upon another person under the
94 circumstances is justifiable if he or she withdraws from the
95 encounter and effectively communicates to the other person his
96 or her intent to do so, but the latter other person
97 nevertheless continues or threatens the use of unlawful
98 physical force.
99 (3) The physical force involved was the product of a
100 combat by agreement not specifically authorized by law.
101 (e) At any time when a defense is claimed under this
102 section, if the defendant concealed, altered, destroyed, or
103 otherwise disposed of the deadly weapon or dangerous
104 instrument used in the commission of the alleged offense,
105 other than by voluntarily providing the unaltered deadly
106 weapon or dangerous instrument to law enforcement, there shall
107 be a rebuttable presumption that the defendant's use of
108 physical force, including deadly physical force, was not
109 justified.
110 (d)(f)(1) A person who uses force, including deadly
111 physical force, as justified and permitted in this section, is
112 immune from criminal prosecution and civil action for the use
Page 4

immune from criminal prosecution and civil action for the use
